data.content:
In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The temporary compatibility switch you configured in .NET 10 no longer exists.

All four of your synchronous calls will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime:

| Breaks | Replacement |
|--------|-------------|
| `.ToList()` | `.ToListAsync()` |
| `.First(...)` | `.FirstAsync(...)` |
| `.Count()` | `.CountAsync()` |
| `.SaveChanges()` | `.SaveChangesAsync()` |

**Fix:** Convert to async all the way up:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to propagate `async`/`await` to all callers (controllers, services, etc.). The Cosmos SDK is fundamentally async-only — EF Core 11 simply stops hiding that behind a blocking `.GetAwaiter().GetResult()` wrapper.
